### Execution via Pixi (Windows-friendly)

- Prefer non-interactive exec: `pixi exec -- python path\to\script.py`.
- Check environment: `pixi exec -- python -V`.
- Run tests: `pixi exec -- pytest -q`.

Fallback (if Pixi unavailable):

```powershell
python -m venv .venv; .\.venv\Scripts\python -m pip install -U pip; `
    .\.venv\Scripts\pip install -r requirements.txt; `
    .\.venv\Scripts\python path\to\script.py
```

### Non-interactive and logs

- Assume no interactive input; pass `--yes`/quiet flags where tools support them.
- Avoid pagers; if a command pages output, append `| cat` (POSIX) or use `| Out-String` in PowerShell.

